## How to Run

### Step 1: Train the Baseline Model
```bash
cd c:\Users\ZeeqRyz\Desktop\BASEPROJECT\05_Baseline_Model
python train_baseline.py
```

This will produce in `outputs/`:
- `training_history.json` + `training_history.png`
- `classification_report.txt` + `classification_report.png`
- `confusion_matrix.png`
- `gradcam_outputs.png`
- `model_summary.txt`
- `eval_summary.json`

### Step 2: Generate Comparison
```bash
python compare_models.py
```

This reads results from both models and produces in `outputs/comparison/`:
- `performance_comparison.png` — bar charts (accuracy, precision, recall, F1)
- `training_curves_comparison.png` — overlaid training curves
- `comparison_summary_table.png` — comprehensive side-by-side table
- `comparison_summary.txt` — text version of the table

---

## Data Split

Both models use **the same data split** (seed 42, 80/10/10) to ensure a fair comparison on identical test images (159 samples).

